he mutex does not mean "I own the dongle."

The mutex only means:

"I am temporarily accessing the dongle's shared data safely."

Those are two completely different things.

Think of it like this:

A bank has one door.

Many customers can enter the bank one at a time to talk to the receptionist.

Entering the bank does not mean you own the bank.

Similarly:

lock mutex

look at scheduler
look at cooldown
possibly insert request
possibly wait

unlock mutex

None of that means you have acquired the dongle.